<refsection condition="ref.description">
<title>Description</title><para>A <tag>tag</tag> identifies an <acronym>XML</acronym> or
      <acronym>SGML</acronym> markup construct. The utility of this element is
      almost wholly constrained to books about markup.</para>

      <refsection><info><title>Processing expectations</title></info>
        

        <para>Formatted inline.</para>

        <para>A <tag>tag</tag> generates all the necessary punctuation
        before and after the construct it identifies. For example, it
        generates both the leading ampersand and the trailing semicolon when
        the <tag class="attribute">class</tag> is
        <literal>genentity</literal>.</para>
</refsection>

